column5: Caught a program on MythBusters last night, no good way to hit a moose with the average car( they used a dummy Moose and a remote controlled car). Slowing down had a better effect than speeding up and trying to send the Moose over the top of the car.  Best bet? Keep your Mooses off the street.
Louse / lice, mouse / mice.  House / hice?
saw the same show......man do they waste alot of money on that program. It is entertaining for the most part though.
Hope and pray for the best. LOL!!!    P.S. That is actually a church in the background!!! Kawartha Kev
Don't worry it will break down before you get to the moose
Don't know about a moose - never hit one - but I know first hand how much damage a cow can do!  A little over $12000 in damages - and I spilt my coffee!   Don
Moose are getting scarce up here. I haven't seen one in over a week now. Global warming, parasites and the increasing Deer population are driving them out. Sad to see.
